const kbContent = "# Chubb Financial Institutions D&O — Smart Submission Intake\n## Knowledge Base\n\n### Process Overview\nThis workflow automates the intake and triage of D&O Financial Institutions renewal submissions. Pace processes the submission from inbound email through regulatory verification, financial analysis, and premium indication — delivering a quote-ready package to the underwriter in under 10 minutes.\n\n### Key Systems\n- **Chubb PAS** — Policy Administration System. Used for incumbent clearance, loss history retrieval, data population (61 fields), and triage tagging.\n- **FDIC Enforcement Actions Portal** (orders.fdic.gov) — Primary source for consent order verification.\n- **SEC EDGAR** — Document verification and 8-K material event scan.\n- **FFIEC UBPR** (cdr.ffiec.gov) — Bank-specific peer benchmarking data.\n- **Chubb Rating Tool** — FI-specific premium calculation model.\n\n### Pinnacle Community Bancorp — Case Summary\n- **Case ID:** SUB-2025-0310-PCBK-FI-0042\n- **Named Insured:** Pinnacle Community Bancorp, Inc. (PCBK, NASDAQ)\n- **Institution Type:** State-chartered commercial bank, Federal Reserve member\n- **Total Assets:** $4.2B (FY2024)\n- **Transaction:** D&O FI Renewal — 4th consecutive year (incumbent)\n- **Effective Date:** May 1, 2025\n- **Prior Policy:** CHB-DOFI-PCBK-2024 — $25M / $1M retention — $312,000\n- **Broker:** Marcus Webb, Gallagher Charlotte\n- **Underwriter:** Sarah Park, Sr. Underwriter — Financial Institutions\n\n### Regulatory History\n- FDIC Consent Order CO-2023-PCBK-01 (BSA/AML, Oct 12, 2023) — **Terminated December 18, 2024**\n- Termination confirmed via: (1) Broker-supplied letter, (2) FDIC enforcement portal, (3) EDGAR 8-K Dec 19, 2024\n- OCC: No enforcement actions (expected — state-chartered, not OCC-supervised)\n- Federal Reserve: No enforcement actions\n- Current status: No outstanding formal enforcement actions\n\n### Loss History\n- 4 policy years with zero claims\n- One D&O derivative claim (May 2023–Apr 2024): $850K total, within $1M retention, Chubb paid $0\n- Settled with prejudice August 2024, no appeal filed\n- All three sources consistent: broker loss run, Loss History Analyzer, EDGAR 8-K\n\n### Financial Profile (FY2024)\n- **Capital:** CET1 12.4% vs. peer median 11.8% — above peer, well-capitalized ✅\n- **Asset Quality:** NPA 0.82% vs. peer median 0.94% — below peer, improving ✅\n- **CRE Concentration:** 278% vs. peer median 295% — elevated but declining 🟡\n- **Earnings:** Net income $39.5M (+16% YoY), ROA 0.94%, NIM 3.41%\n- **Overall:** Good financial health — solid capital, improving asset quality\n\n### Triage Decision\n- All 14 appetite factors evaluated — no referral triggers\n- **Decision:** ✅ Proceed to Quote\n- **Endorsement:** Regulatory representation and warranty — no BSA/AML exclusion (consent order terminated)\n- **Premium Indication:** $336,000 (+7.7% over prior year)\n- **Underwriter Discount Applied:** $329,000 (+5.4%) — relationship/capital discount\n\n### Underwriter Workflow\nSarah Park receives a Pace-generated summary with:\n1. Full regulatory verification results (triple-sourced)\n2. Financial analysis vs. peer benchmarks\n3. Loss history cross-reference\n4. Endorsement recommendation\n5. Draft quote letter pre-populated with all fields\n6. Rating tool output ($336K indication)\n\nSarah reviews and approves before Pace sends the quote to Marcus Webb.\n\n### Common Questions\n\n**Why no BSA/AML exclusion?**\nThe consent order is terminated. Applying an exclusion would penalize a resolved issue. Pace recommends a regulatory rep/warranty endorsement instead.\n\n**Why maintain $1M retention?**\nThe one prior claim ($850K) was within retention and Chubb paid $0. The claim is closed with prejudice. Maintaining retention is appropriate.\n\n**Is the CRE concentration a concern?**\nAt 278%, it's elevated relative to the 300% regulatory guidance threshold but is below peer median (295%) and declining from 291% in FY2023. It warrants a note but does not trigger referral.\n\n**What governance improvements did Pinnacle make?**\nFormer FDIC examiner appointed to board, new CCO with HSBC pedigree, NICE Actimize transaction monitoring deployed, third-party validation completed — all to FDIC satisfaction.\n";
